*Henry "Harry" (ca.1848 &ndash; ca.2 June 1888)<!-- married Elizabeth ?? (died 22? 27? April 1890) on ??.--> He was for a time manager of Delamere Station, near [[Katherine, Northern Territory]], but was tin mining in the area when he perished, apparently lost and bewildered.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article3313156 |title=Northern Territory Times. |newspaper=[[The Northern Territory Times|Northern Territory Times and Gazette (Darwin, NT : 1873 - 1927)]] |location=Darwin, NT |date=23 June 1888 |accessdate=23 May 2012 |page=3 |publisher=National Library of Australia}}</ref>
